<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="sec-operations-with-vectors"
    xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Basic Arithmetic Operations</title>

    <introduction xml:id="introduction-vector-arithmetic">
        <p>
            In this section, we will introduce how to perform the arithmetic operations on vectors in Sage.
        </p>
        <p>
            <idx>
                <h>Vectors</h>
                <h>Arithmetic Operations</h>
            </idx>
            Vectors can be added and subtracted using the <c>+</c> and <c>-</c> operators.
            The result of adding or subtracting two vectors is a new vector with the same number of components.
        </p>
        <sage>
            <input>
                v = vector([1, 2, 3])
                w = vector([4, 5, 6])
                v + w
            </input>
        </sage>
        <sage>
            <input>
                v - w
            </input>
        </sage>

        <p>
            <idx>
                <h>Vectors</h>
                <h>Scalar Multiplication</h>
            </idx>
            Vectors can be multiplied by real numbers (scalar multiplication) using the <c>*</c> operator. Here
            is an example of scalar multiplication of a vector by 2.
        </p>
        <sage>
            <input>
                2 * v
            </input>
        </sage>
    </introduction>
</section>
